main event: On 29th August 1952 in Selma, Calif., three green lights and one red light were observed moving up and down with no specific shape, sound, or reported speed. The observation was visually made from the ground and the object was seen overhead.
interesting points: The lights were observed moving up and down with no defined shape or reported speed, and no sound was heard.
The report mentions passing on the information to various organizations for further investigation.
The observation was made by a F-94 vetted individual with radar and visual contact.
Insufficient data for evaluation was stated in the report, suggesting a lack of conclusive evidence.
There were no photographs accompanying this report.
sighted object: three green lights and one red light
witnesses: Stanley Dile, a F-94 vetted individual
